pulfalight.title: Collection-level title display is showing dates incorrectly.

comments.body: We are now experiencing issues with directing researchers to how they can contact us. We would like to add the Ask Us button to the finding aids. The libapp ask us should go to the Special Collections libanswers queue.
I am still seeing the banner on the site.
the mudd portion is still showing
@ccleeton We just had to deploy it, it should be good now.

It looks like any request that goes to https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/suggest triggers this error. 

If `/catalog/suggest` is not a valid URL perhaps we should handle this different rather than reporting an HTTP 500

Or, if we are really expecting to handle this URL (see https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/blob/main/app/controllers/catalog_controller.rb#L272) maybe there is indeed a bug to fix.

pulfalight.title: Generating collection-level MARC records from EADs/Resource records

comments.body: Yang from cataloging reported an issue with how the subject headings are coded in MARC records created from EADs. Geographic headings should be $z in MARC, but they are in $x.
I'll mark this unblocked, but we still need details from @regineheberlein about how this used to work.

My understanding is that the old process of converting collection-level EADs to MARC21 that I worked on with @regineheberlein is no longer needed since ASpace has the ability to export MARC21, but I may be mistaken.

Maybe that's the case? Attached is an example of what ASpace outputs:

https://gist.github.com/tpendragon/4331a23afce506e0c34a62981fb7ce92
